{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Dogfood the completed lifecycle in rebar\n\n## Goal\nProve the integrated behavior through public surfaces and enable both optional policies for this project without requiring migration or backfill.\n\n## Implementation\n- Enable verify.enforce_plan_material_pins and verify.require_plan_review_for_close in rebar.toml; retain false defaults in the reusable configuration schema.\n- Add public-surface lifecycle scenarios for: legacy unpinned attestations; emission while enforcement is off; enable/disable/re-enable; direct child drift; depends_on and blocks normalization; natural A-to-B-to-C transitivity; successful unchanged re-review stopping propagation; execution-time self-edit; in_progress-to-open reset; code-only drift at close; deleted and archived pinned targets; concurrent review/close changes; and audited force-close.\n- Verify no eager backfill, graph-wide invalidation event, new pin command, list-output change, or stored relation migration occurs.\n- Treat the sibling stories as the sole owners of adding each configuration key to the reusable schema and `tests/golden/config_surface.json`. This story verifies both keys are already present together, enables them only in `rebar.toml`, and updates `CHANGELOG.md` plus `docs/release-notes.md` for the rebar-project policy cutover; it does not re-register either golden key.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Rebar enables both policies while library defaults remain off, and a pre-feature unpinned attestation continues to pass both gates.\n- [ ] End-to-end tests prove direct and natural-transitive invalidation only after actual narrow material changes.\n- [ ] An unchanged successful re-review produces no further propagation.\n- [ ] Outgoing `depends_on` and inbound `blocks` references to one canonical prerequisite normalize to one prerequisite pin/evaluation.\n- [ ] Execution adaptation, return-to-open reset, and code-only close freshness are proven through public lifecycle surfaces.\n- [ ] Enable, disable, and re-enable behavior is proven through public lifecycle surfaces.\n- [ ] Deleted and archived target handling, concurrency rechecks, and audited force-close are proven through public lifecycle surfaces.\n- [ ] No eager backfill, graph-wide invalidation event, new pin command, ordinary-list output change, or stored relation migration is introduced.\n\n## Verification\n- Run the complete lifecycle interface suite with both rebar policies enabled.\n- Run make check and the full non-integration test suite.\n- In an isolated fixture tracker, invoke the real checkout CLI with no `--dry-run` bypass and both policies loaded as `true`. Exercise four cases: (1) a legacy unpinned attestation claims successfully with exit 0 and `open -> in_progress`; (2) current pins plus compatible execution-phase plan and completion attestations close successfully with exit 0 and `in_progress -> closed`; (3) stale material-pin drift rejects claim or close with exit 1, leaves status unchanged, and names the canonical stale target plus `stale-pin-drift`; (4) missing or phase-incompatible close-plan review rejects close with exit 1, leaves `in_progress` unchanged, and instructs the operator to run `review-plan`. Do not use force-close in these four gate-health cases.\n- Record one JSON object in a ticket comment with `config.enforce_plan_material_pins`, `config.require_plan_review_for_close`, and a `cases` array. Each case contains `name`, `command`, `expected_exit`, `observed_exit`, `before_status`, `expected_after_status`, `observed_after_status`, `expected_reason_tokens`, `observed_reason`, and `passed`. Gate health passes only when both config fields are `true`, every observed exit/status exactly equals its expected value, every required reason token is present, and all four `passed` values are true. Any mismatch fails verification and blocks closing this story.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784576411708889001,"uuid":"0eddc3a5-7a5f-4f7b-bc1a-82d40d8449f6"}